hopobject.body: I've just graduated tucowsdomains.com The phrase "a fish starts to stink at the head" ("balik bashtan kokar") comes from Turkey, reminding us that petty bribes at street-level are often matched by greater corruption at the top of organisations and institutions. Mexican officials looking to earn a kickback for arranging a business deal will demand they are given "a bite" ("una mordida"), while their Columbian counterparts are said to "saw" ("serrucho") off a part of a government contract for themselves.
